headline.main: Peak Gasoline Demand Looms With Engine Efficiency Gains
headline.print_headline: Peak Gasoline Demand Looms With Engine Efficiency Gains

lead_paragraph: Demand for gasoline in the United States, which accounts for a tenth of global oil consumption, is expected to peak next year as engines become more efficient, WoodMackenzie analysts said.
